The paper proposes an efficient family of algorithms for learning the parameters of a Bayesian network from incomplete data. This problem falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of probabilistic graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of non-iterative methods and closed form parameter estimates, which are common in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the elimination of the need for inference in a Bayesian network, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's focus on missing data problems and consistent parameter estimates is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's use of statistical methods and information theory is relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
